        "subject": "LU-18951 utils: declare argv[argc] as NULL",
        "message": "LU-18951 utils: declare argv[argc] as NULL\n\nThe C standard requires that argv[argc] is NULL, but lsnapshot.c was\ncreating argument lists with only argc elements in it.  This could\ncause command execution to crash in some cases.\n\nDeclare argv[] to have enough elements and initialize it to NULL.\n\nMinor updates to related man pages.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-lsnapshot\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nChange-Id: I7ab0c4fb1b29d55a537011f244847dd4b13ebbe5\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64949\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Timothy Day <timday@thelustrecollective.com>\nReviewed-by: Mikhail Pershin <mpershin@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
